32
00:02:20.100 --> 00:02:21.360
for our clients.

33
00:02:22.720 --> 00:02:28.100
Properties with severe damage from fire,
floods, or long-term neglect are prime

34
00:02:28.100 --> 00:02:30.600
candidates for our as-is purchasing model.

35
00:02:31.380 --> 00:02:36.520
We also help landlords who are ready to exit
the market and stop managing tenants,

36
00:02:37.040 --> 00:02:40.560
looking for a clean and simple way out of
their property burdens.

37
00:02:42.020 --> 00:02:43.180
How do we qualify them?

38
00:02:43.680 --> 00:02:46.140
Our hard filters are strict to ensure
success.

39
00:02:46.540 --> 00:02:51.060
The seller must want to close within 30 days
and must be the legal owner or have

40
00:02:51.060 --> 00:02:51.520
authority.

41
00:02:52.400 --> 00:02:57.120
They should not be currently working with a
realtor and must be willing to trade a

42
00:02:57.120 --> 00:03:02.400
portion of their equity for the incredible
speed and convenience we offer at the BMH

43
00:03:02.400 --> 00:03:02.700
Group.

44
00:03:03.040 --> 00:03:08.240
There are people we must avoid to protect
our time and theirs.

45
00:03:08.920 --> 00:03:14.400
Disqualifiers include properties already
listed with a realtor or sellers who simply

46
00:03:14.400 --> 00:03:16.560
lack the legal authority to sell.

47
00:03:17.580 --> 00:03:23.320
Listen for key phrases like, I just want to
sell the house as is, I don't want to deal

48
00:03:23.320 --> 00:03:26.560
with realtors, or I need to sell fast.

49
00:03:26.800 --> 00:03:29.000
These are our signals for success.

50
00:03:30.460 --> 00:03:32.680
Our messaging must resonate with their
needs.

51
00:03:33.240 --> 00:03:37.480
Focus on the speed of closing and the
certainty of a cash offer without any of the

52
00:03:37.480 --> 00:03:39.380
traditional delays or complications.

53
00:03:40.520 --> 00:03:46.860
Always emphasize that we require no repairs,
no commissions, and

54
00:03:46.860 --> 00:03:53.340
no cleanup. This simple, empathetic process
is what truly resonates with our

55
00:03:53.340 --> 00:03:55.120
distressed property sellers.

56
00:03:56.540 --> 00:04:01.440
During discovery, start by asking about the
property's condition and uncovering their

57
00:04:01.440 --> 00:04:06.660
true motivation. We need to see exactly what
is driving the potential sale to help them

58
00:04:06.660 --> 00:04:07.180
best.

59
00:04:08.160 --> 00:04:12.980
Ask how soon they hope to close and if there
are specific repairs or legal issues.

60
00:04:13.460 --> 00:04:18.100
This helps ensure they meet our strict timeline
and condition filters for a fast close.

61
00:04:19.440 --> 00:04:23.960
Check the occupancy status and verify if you
are speaking with the legal owner.

62
00:04:24.420 --> 00:04:29.460
This information is vital for the next steps
in our business process to ensure a smooth

63
00:04:29.460 --> 00:04:30.220
transition.

64
00:04:31.060 --> 00:04:36.480
Ask if they have considered a realtor or if
they are specifically looking for a faster

65
00:04:36.480 --> 00:04:41.520
option. We want to be their simple,
effective, and trustworthy solution.

66
00:04:43.360 --> 00:04:45.800
Finally, ask the powerful closing question.

67
00:04:46.580 --> 00:04:51.680
If we could make the process simple and
close quickly, would that solve the situation

68
00:04:51.680 --> 00:04:52.280
for you?

69
00:04:53.260 --> 00:04:56.220
More on this later when we talk about
